    <h2>LG Dryer Problems We Fix</h2>

    <p>Our technicians service all LG dryer models — electric, gas, front-load, stackable, and LG ThinQ smart dryers. Here are the most common issues we handle on service calls across Los Angeles and Orange County:</p>

    <h3>LG Dryer Not Heating</h3>
    <p>The most frequent call we receive. On electric LG dryers, the cause is usually a failed heating element (OEM part 5301EL1001J), blown thermal fuse, or faulty high-limit thermostat. On gas models, a failed igniter or gas valve coils are the typical culprits. We carry parts for the most common LG models and resolve most no-heat repairs in a single visit.</p>

    <h3>LG Dryer Making Noise</h3>
    <p>Squeaking, thumping, grinding, or rattling all point to specific worn components. Drum rollers (AGM75510755) are the most common cause of thumping on LG front-load dryers. Squeaking usually indicates a worn idler pulley or drum bearing. We diagnose the exact source and replace only what's necessary — not the entire drum assembly.</p>

    <h3>LG Dryer Not Starting</h3>
    <p>A door switch failure, thermal fuse, or faulty main control board are the usual causes when an LG dryer won't power on. We test each component systematically to avoid replacing parts that don't need replacement.</p>

    <h3>LG Dryer Takes Too Long to Dry</h3>
    <p>Usually caused by a clogged or kinked dryer vent, worn door seal, or failing moisture sensor. A d80, d90, or d95 error code is Google's way of telling you the vent is restricted. We check and clean the vent on every service call, not just the internal parts.</p>

    <h3>LG Dryer Error Codes</h3>
    <p>d80, d90, d95 (airflow restriction), tE1/tE3 (thermistor), HS (humidity sensor), PS (power supply). Our technicians are familiar with the full LG error code library and diagnose the root cause — not just reset the error.</p>

    <h3>LG Dryer Stops Mid-Cycle</h3>
    <p>Thermal overload protection triggers when the dryer overheats — usually from a clogged vent or failing thermostat. We find the root cause so it doesn't recur after the reset.</p>

    <h2>LG Dryer Models We Service</h2>

    <p>We repair all current and recent LG dryer lines including DLGX, DLEX, DLE, DLG, DLEC (all-in-one), DLHC, and Signature series. ThinQ-enabled models (Wi-Fi, SmartDiagnosis) are fully supported. If your LG dryer model isn't listed here, call us — we service the complete LG dryer lineup.</p>

    <h2>How Our Repair Process Works</h2>

    <p><strong>1. Call or book online.</strong> We confirm a same-day appointment window, usually 2 hours wide. You'll get a technician arrival call 30 minutes before.</p>
    <p><strong>2. Diagnosis.</strong> The technician runs a full diagnostic — electrical, mechanical, and airflow — and identifies the exact cause. This takes 20–30 minutes and costs $65.</p>
    <p><strong>3. Upfront quote.</strong> You receive a firm price for parts and labor before any work begins. No pressure, no surprises. If you approve, the $65 diagnostic is waived.</p>
    <p><strong>4. Repair on the spot.</strong> In 85% of cases, we have the required OEM part in the van and complete the repair the same visit. For specialty parts, we return within 1–2 business days.</p>
    <p><strong>5. Test and warranty.</strong> We run a full test cycle before leaving. Every repair is warranted — if the same issue returns, we come back at no additional charge.</p>

